kerosene
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:The usual name in NZ, (spelled chiefly now <i>-ene</i>, though earlier <i>- ine</i> frequent) for what seems called mainly in Britian <i>paraffin (oil)</i>. (Paraffin oil in NZ is usually the colourless, tasteless oil (Concise O.D `liquid paraffin") used formerly as a laxative.) Charles Ransom: US for liquid paraffin is mineral oil. in NZ, <i>kerosene</i> is often shortened coll. to <i>kero</i>.


